Question: How can I read a text file in Java line by line using BufferedReader?:
Please using this api: BufferedReader.readLine.
Answer:<<<api>>>: BufferedReader.readLine
<<<code>>>: BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("file.txt"));
String line;
while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {
    System.out.println(line);
}
reader.close();
<<<explanation>>>: The readLine() method of the BufferedReader class reads a line of text from the input stream and returns it as a string. It returns null if the end of the stream has been reached.
